<p><font color="red">You are about to install an experimental version
of OpenCCU on your CCU device! Using such experimental versions
could impose severe issues that might cause your configuration to
be broken or lost. If you instead want to install a stable version
of OpenCCU please download the latest stable version from the
following URL:</font></p>
<p>
<a href="https://github.com/OpenCCU/OpenCCU/releases/latest">https://github.com/OpenCCU/OpenCCU/releases/latest</a>
</p>
<hr/>
<p>General information:</p>
<p>You are about to install a third-party firmware on your CCU device.
This <a href=https://openccu.de/>OpenCCU</a> firmware
consists of the same feature set like the original eQ-3 vendor CCU
firmware with the same version number. On top of that it
comes with some additional features and first hand bugfixes that
the vendor firmware has not yet integrated.</p>
<p>Please keep in mind that you can reinstall the vendor CCU firmware
at any time and thus return to the vendor-supported firmware. In
addition, your configuration and settings will be automatically
converted to be usable with the OpenCCU firmware. We do,
however, suggest that you create a fresh backup before actually
installing this firmware on your CCU device.</p>
<hr/>
<p><b>For recent ChangeLog and Releases overview visit:</b> <a href="https://github.com/OpenCCU/OpenCCU/releases">https://github.com/OpenCCU/OpenCCU/releases</a>.</p>
<p><b>Changes in this release compared to the previous version:</b></p>
